The South African Weather Service says Gauteng province will experience showers and thunder-showers overnight until Monday morning. Temperatures are expected to stay in the low 20’s until Monday and then start increasing. Forecaster, Wayne Venter, says the province will experience mostly cloudy conditions. “For today (Sunday), we are looking at most cloudy conditions. We had a bit of light rain this morning and early this morning, especially over the central parts of Gauteng. That is to clear out and we are expecting some showers and thundershowers to move back in over the southern part of Gauteng during this afternoon.”  